## Fix 6: `emitDP` — Carry flag for SUB/CMP is Inverted on PPC

ARM carry for subtraction is *inverted borrow*: C=1 means no borrow. PPC's XER CA for `subfc` is also inverted borrow. But `setC_xer` reads XER[CA] which is at bit 29 (from MSB) = bit 2 (from LSB). Verify the bit position:

```cpp
// jit_ppc.cpp - Fix setC_xer (XER CA is bit 29 from MSB = bit 2 from LSB)
static void setC_xer(Ctx& ctx) {
    ctx.E(ppc_mfxer(TA));
    // XER bit 29 (MSB numbering) = CA flag
    // We want to place it at CPSR bit 29 (LSB) = bit 2 (MSB)  
    // CPSR C flag is bit 29 (LSB numbering)
    // In RCPSR as a 32-bit value: bit 29 from LSB
    
    // Extract XER[CA] (bit 29 MSB = bit 2 LSB) to bit 29 LSB of RCPSR
    ctx.E(ppc_rlwinm(TA, TA, 0, 29, 29));      // keep only XER[CA] at bit 2 (LSB)
    // Now shift to bit 29 position (LSB): shift left by 27
    ctx.E(ppc_rlwinm(TA, TA, 27, 2, 2));       // TA = CA << 27... 
    
    // Actually the original approach is simpler - let's verify:
    // XER: bit 34 of 64-bit? No, on PPC32:
    // XER[SO]=bit0, XER[OV]=bit1, XER[CA]=bit2 (MSB numbering from bit31)
    // So XER[CA] is at position 2 from MSB = bit 29 from LSB
    // CPSR[C] is bit 29 from LSB
    // So XER[CA] is ALREADY at bit 29 from LSB!
    
    // Original code: rlwinm(TA,TA,0,29,29) keeps bit29(LSB) = correct
    // Then OR into RCPSR after clearing bit 29
    ctx.E(ppc_mfxer(TA));                       // re-fetch (we clobbered TA)
    ctx.E(ppc_rlwinm(TA, TA, 0, 2, 2));        // keep XER[CA] at bit29 LSB (=bit2 MSB)
    ctx.E(ppc_rlwinm(RCPSR, RCPSR, 0, 3, 1));  // clear CPSR[C] (bit29 LSB = bit2 MSB)  
    // Wait: rlwinm(D,S,0,3,1) with MB=3,ME=1 wraps: keeps bits 3..31 and 0..1
    // That clears bit 2 (MSB) = bit 29 (LSB) — CORRECT
    ctx.E(ppc_or(RCPSR, RCPSR, TA));
}
```

The original `setC_xer` was actually correct. Leave it as-is.

